Kingston is a Negroni variation made with rum instead of gin. Recently, I found a variation from Kingston named Artsy Bird by @seanogle. It uses the @twojames Doctor Bird Jamaican rum and switches out the Campari for the dark, herbal, and bitter artichoke liqueur Cynar 75. 

Combine with Antica Formula vermouth to create a well-balanced and super unique, bitter, delicious dark drink. Dash of orange bitters, two dashes of chocolate bitters, and an orange peel to garnish. 

What you’re left with is a delicious cocktail without the down and dirty. 

Artsy Bird 🐦 

1 oz Doctor Bird Rum
1 oz Cynar 70
1 oz Carpano Antica
1 Dash Orange Bitters
2 Dashes Chocolate Bitters 
1 Dried Orange slice (For Garnish) 

Directions: 
Combine all ingredients into a mixing glass
Add ice, and stir until chilled
Strain into a Nick and Nora Glass
Dried orange slice for garnish

Diffords Top 100: VODKA SOUR (71/100)
- 60ml/2oz Vodka
- 30ml/1oz Lemon Juice
- 15ml/0.5oz Rich Simple Syrup
- 2 dashes Angostura Bitters
- 1 eggwhite
- - - - -
HOW: Shake all with ice / Shake all without ice / Double strain in glass over ice / Garnish.
- - -
RATING: 1.5/5
- - - - -
Yes, it looks pretty. Yes, it's a fun garnish. Yes, your friends who don't like 'the flavor of alcohol in their cocktails' will probably enjoy it 🤪 but my oh my, apart from the fact the ratios are spot on, this drink has little to nothing to offer.🥱 It's just Spiked Lemonade with a linger of Angostura 🙃.
.
It's very simple: Vodka is useless in a Sour.🤷‍♀️ I'd even add that the only reason I'm not giving it a 0.5/5 (not for being undrinkable, just for being one of the most boring drinks ever 😴), is the faint salvation provided by two simple dashes of Angostura "Saving Grace" Bitters 🩸.
.
Look, I don't hate Vodka at all. On the contrary even, I'll ALWAYS protect its use in mixology.🍹 Whether it's a neutral industrial distillate, or an aromatic "grain to glass" expression 🌾, I believe in it and sometimes even love it.💕 But just not in this drink. Literally ANY other spirit in the world is a better fit for the Sour template than Vodka.💁‍♀️ End of rant.
.
Drinkstagram ❤️ do me a favor and just sub the vodka for anything else, or if you want to make a vodka cocktail, whip up anything but this standard Sour 🍸.
- - - - -
